cz.cvut.felk.cig.jcop.problem.bucket
Class BucketIterator

java.lang.Object
  cz.cvut.felk.cig.jcop.problem.bucket.BucketIterator
All Implemented Interfaces:
OperationIterator, java.util.Iterator<Operation>
public class BucketIterator
extends java.lang.Object
implements OperationIterator

Iterator over bucket operations.

Operations are iterated in this way:

  1. Pour operations
  2. Spill operations
  3. Fill operations

Each operation type is sorted by source bucket. Eg. first filled bucket is bucket with index 0, then index 1 etc. Pouring is first pour bucket with index 0 to buckets 1 ... n, then pour bucket 1 to other etc.

Field Detail

counter

protected int counter
Main counter. For fill and spill operations used to indicate which bucket to fill/spill. For pour operations indicates destination bucket.

counter2

protected int counter2
Secondary counter. Not used for fill/spill operations, for pour operations indicates source bucket.

stage

protected int stage
Stage of iterator.

0 = prepare stage (move counter not yet called), 1 = pour operations, 2 = spill operations, 3 = fill operations, .

configuration

protected Configuration configuration
Configuration to iterate operations over.

problem

protected Bucket problem
Problem for configuration, required to get bucket capacities.

getRandomOperation

public Operation getRandomOperation()
Description copied from interface: OperationIterator
Returns randomly chosen operation.

Note that internal counter is not changed, therefore subsequent calls to next will be unaffected by getRandomOperation.

Also, two calls of getRandomOperation could possibly return the same operation.
